The paper deals with a multiple access scheme for satellite communications, which involves coding and decoding mechanisms. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves interference cancellation and throughput analysis, which could also place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also deals with communication protocols and mechanisms, which could place it in the Communications (cs.COMM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves simulations and analysis of a proposed scheme, which could also place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS) sub-category.
